&ldquo;It was an amazing duel. He (Mitchell) just willed his team every game, win or lose. He had that fight and you&rsquo;ve got to show respect. We talk off the court, too. We&rsquo;re both Adidas guys, we see each other often,&rdquo; the 23-year-old Nuggets guard said.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;I pay respects for him. It was a great battle, and it&rsquo;s not going to be the only one either. We expect to see each other a lot down the future. He raises my game, I raise his. We go at it, and it&rsquo;s a lot of fun. We bring the best out of each other.&rdquo;

Nikola Jokic is extremely patient on offense. He&rsquo;s not the fast-paced, explosive player that we see a lot in the NBA. In fact, he&rsquo;s quite the opposite, and the methodical, visionary style of play has made him an elite playmaker.<br />
<br />
&ldquo;I&rsquo;m patient because I cannot really run fast,&rdquo; Jokic recently joked with reporters. &ldquo;That&rsquo;s my only option.&rdquo;

